      <p></p><p>Problem with your chart there is that data has been "corrected" from the raw data. &nbsp;Around the 1950's is considered to be the point at which human produced CO2 was created in such mass as to be the start of AGW.</p><p><br></p><p>So for a warmest, you want the temp before 1950 to be colder and after 1950 to be warmer. &nbsp;If the raw data does not reflect a good enough change, then "correct" it as it is obviously wrong...</p><p><br></p><p><a href="http://www.c3headlines.com/2011/12/science-by-lubchencos-noaa-fake-global-warming-by-changing-historical-temperature-data.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.c3headlines.com/2011/12/science-by-lubchencos-noaa-fake-global-warming-by-changing-historical-temperature-data.html</a><br></p>
